  "market_context": "Crude Oil Futures on the 60-minute chart consolidated through Asia and London sessions, setting up expectations that New York would manipulate and deliver the directional move.",
  "key_observation": "New York swept a low with displacement, forming a bullish order block from a series of down-close candles. A subsequent closure above the order block's opening price created a propulsion block, with the opening price acting as a sensitive entry trigger.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Observed Asia and London sessions consolidating, anticipating New York to manipulate and produce the directional move.",
    "Step 2: Identified a low being swept with displacement out of the area during New York session.",
    "Step 3: Recognized a series of down-close candles into the low followed by displacement closure over them, forming a bullish order block.",
    "Step 4: Watched for price to react: a down-close candle delivered into the order block and into a fair value gap with displacement out.",
    "Step 5: Waited for closure over the opening price to confirm the propulsion block.",
    "Step 6: Planned an entry at the opening price with stop on the low or on the body (mean threshold), requiring the mean threshold not to be broken; safer stop at the intermediate-term low. Target set at 2R.",
    "Step 7: Confirmed entry triggered, price respected the mean threshold, closed back outside the propulsion block, consolidated briefly, then expanded higher."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit the 2R target after price respected the mean threshold and expanded higher.",
  "lessons": "When Asia and London consolidate, anticipate New York to manipulate. A propulsion block formed from a closure over an existing order block's opening price provides a high-probability entry — the opening price must remain sensitive and the mean threshold must hold.",
